Energy regulator Nersa has granted Eskom an 18.65% tariff increase. eNCA spoke to Cosatu spokesperson, Sizwe Pamla. #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Trade union federation Cosatu has slammed the National Energy Regulator's decision to grant Eskom an above-inflation increase of 18.65 percent. The increase comes into effect from the first of April this year. READ: Nersa approves 18.65% tariff increase for Eskom This is bad news for South Africa's already over-burdened consumers. Cosatu spokesperson Sizwe Pamla says the decision was reckless.